org.retal.logiweb.dao.interfaces

Interface PartRowsReader<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CarDAO, UserDAO

    public interface PartRowsReader<T>
    Interface, indicating that DAO implementing it is able to read the given amount of rows from given position.
    Author:
    Alexander Retivov

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      List<T> readRows(int from, int amount)
      Reads part of table and returns it as list.

    • Method Detail

      • readRows

        List<T> readRows(int from,
                 int amount)
        Reads part of table and returns it as list.
        Parameters:
        from - number of row from which reading is started (the row itself is excluded)
        amount - amount of rows to be read from database
        Returns:
        list of read rows
